    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Defines a ceremonial dance performed by Southeastern Native North American tribes, including Cherokee, Chickasaw, Yuchi, and Creek (Mvskoke) communities. Often performed as part of the Green Corn Dance, but can also be interspersed throughout other ceremonies. Consists of dancers who follow a lead dancer in a circular motion around a fire. Dancers' motions are often accompanied by turtle shell shakers worn at the ankles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
